The paper deals with unsupervised image to image translation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel bound for predicting the success of unsupervised cross-domain mapping methods, which involves machine learning techniques such as hyperparameter tuning and stopping criteria, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of multiple algorithms and their performance, which falls under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
